# Mail Package (`internal/mail`)

## Rationale

Outbound email is sent through **Resend** (OpenAPI client in `openapi/gen/resend/`). Most sends are **persisted first** in `send_email_request` so a background worker can retry after failures or rate limits.

## Contracts

- Public surface for the app is [`dependency.Mailer`](internal/dependency/dependency.go) — add or change methods there first, then implement on `*Mailer` in this package and run `make generate-mocks`.
- Persistence and worker eligibility are [`dependency.Mail`](internal/dependency/dependency.go), implemented in [`internal/store/communication/mail.go`](internal/store/communication/mail.go).
- HTTP transport to Resend is abstracted as [`dependency.Sender`](internal/dependency/dependency.go) (`PostEmails`) for tests.

## File layout

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `mail.go` | `Mailer` construction, Resend client wiring, template parse (`embed`), `buildSendMailRequest`, low-level `send` / `sendRaw`, `sendWithInsert` / `queueEmail` |
| `send.go` | `templateName` / `templateSubjects`, exported `Send*` and `Queue*` methods |
| `worker.go` | `Start` / `Stop`, ticker loop over unsent rows |
| `send_retry.go` | Transient vs permanent classification, backoff, mailer retry defaults |

## Configuration

- `Config` fields use `mapstructure` tags; **new settings** must be added to the main config struct in `config/cfg.go` with env binding — never read env vars inside `internal/mail`.
- Retry/worker tuning (`WorkerInterval`, `MaxSendAttempts`, `RetryBaseInterval`, `RetryMaxInterval`) belongs in config, not hardcoded magic numbers in call sites.

## Templates

- Templates live under `internal/mail/templates/`: **root** `*.gohtml` files and **`partials/*.gohtml`**.
- Parsing loads partials once, then **clones** that tree for each root template (`parseTemplates` in `mail.go`).
- Adding a new email type requires **all** of: new `templates/<name>.gohtml`, a `templateName` const, and a `templateSubjects` entry in `send.go`.
- Execute with the root file name as the template entry point (`ExecuteTemplate(..., string(tn), data)`).

## HTML and untrusted input

- Use `html/template` (not `text/template`) so all pipeline output is auto-escaped. Do not inject `template.HTML` or raw user HTML into bodies unless the product explicitly requires it and you have a safe pipeline.

## Send vs queue

- **`sendWithInsert`**: insert row, attempt immediate send; on transport failure **log and return `nil`** so the caller is not blocked — the worker picks up the unsent row.
- **`queueEmail`**: insert only; worker sends later (use for fire-and-forget / must-not-block paths).
- Convert between Resend requests and DB rows with helpers in `internal/dto` (`ResendSendEmailRequestToEntity`, `EntitySendEmailRequestToResend`).

## Worker and `dependency.Mail`

- Eligible unsent rows: `GetAllUnsent(ctx, false, maxSendAttempts, time.Now().UTC())` (under attempt cap and past `next_retry_at`).
- On send failure, record state via **`ScheduleSendRetry`** (backoff + increment attempts) or **`MarkSendDead`** when retries are exhausted — keep behavior aligned with `Config.MaxSendAttempts` / retry intervals.
- **HTTP 429** from Resend maps to `mailApiLimitReached` (`codes.ResourceExhausted`); the worker should **stop processing the current batch** when this is returned so you do not hammer the API.

## Generated code

- **Do not edit** `openapi/gen/resend/` — regenerate from OpenAPI when the contract changes.

## Logging and errors

- Use `log/slog` with `ErrorContext` / structured fields for send and worker failures.
- Wrap errors with `fmt.Errorf("...: %w", err)` when propagating.

## Testing

- Unit tests use `mocks.NewMockMail` and construct the mailer via `new` or `New` with a test `Config` (see `mail_test.go`).
- Do not call the real Resend API from tests — mock `dependency.Sender` when testing send paths.

